Roles & Responsibilities
ABOUT ALGOMARKETING
—
We are experts at delivering programs and resourcing for strategic roles within Marketing teams.
We are a global team of Marketing experts, spanning 30 countries across Asia Pacific, Americas, Africa, and Europe. Highly experienced in enterprise B2B Marketing, and specialised in technology and SaaS.
Our team works collaboratively, with experience from the world's largest and most ambitious brands, including Google, Workday, Worldpay, Accenture, ACI Worldwide, GSK, and Allianz.
We empower Marketers through Algorithmic Marketing, a data driven approach that delivers deeper insights, faster execution,and streamlined operations. Visit our website to read more about us.

ABOUT CLIENT
—
Our client is a leading Global B2B fintech brand. More details to follow.

ABOUT THE ROLE
—

We are looking for an experienced, proactive, and results-oriented contractor to support Client’s
world-class APAC demand generation engine. This role will be responsible for helping to drive marketing
leads by: keeping a pulse on lead flow health; diagnosing mid-funnel lead flow issues; proactively
making recommendations to optimise lead conversion using data; and generally helping to build a strong
interlock with the sales development organization. The role will cover client’s businesses in
Australia+New Zealand, Southeast Asia, and Japan, reporting directly to the Startups, Small and Medium
Business demand generation lead. The ideal candidate will be data-driven, skilled at building reports and
dashboards in Salesforce, have a relentless focus on optimisation, and passionate about partnering with
sales teams to drive outcomes for the business.


You will:
Help plan and develop the APAC lead management and optimisation program to grow opportunities and pipeline across the region;
Build a body of reports to troubleshoot or analyse data, deep dive into and solve business problems, and/or identify opportunities;
Implement a cadence of communication with the sales development organisation to proactively diagnose lead flow opportunities and recommend actions to be taken;
Work cross-functionally with the central Lead Management team to address lead routing issues in a timely manner;
Work closely with the regional APAC field marketing team and sales development in the joint effort to grow pipeline;
Track, measure, and communicate program results, continually optimising for scale and performance, and seeking to generate new global best practices to be shared with other regions.
We are looking for someone with:
3-5 years’ relevant experience with a strong track record for driving results through analytics;
Outstanding analytical skills and the ability to craft actionable insights from complex data;
Competence in Salesforce, Tableau, and spreadsheeting;
Ability to interpret data, craft actionable insights, and make recommendations;
Experience partnering with sales teams, driving disciplined lead follow up;
Strong understanding of lead management and sales funnel management; and
Excellent organisational and project management skills.
You also likely have:
Experience earning trust as a strategic business partner;
A startup mentality with a bias to action and the ability to flex in a fast-paced environment;
Ability to work collaboratively and cross-functionally.
